The paper proposes a generic EEG signal classification framework using a reinforced selective attention model and convolutional mapping operation. This involves machine learning techniques such as neural networks and deep learning, which are commonly associated with the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper also involves feature engineering and signal processing, which are associated with cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CV (Computer Vision). Finally, the paper focuses on Brain-Computer Interface applications, which falls under the sub-category of cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction).
